>Description:
In DrScheme's editor window, shortcuts like command-c, command-q or command-v don't work when capslock is on. This is a misfeature, as at least on OS X it is common practise that command keyboard shortcuts also work when capslock is on.
>How-To-Repeat:
Open DrScheme. Press the capslock key. Write something in capital letters. Pressing command-s or any other command shortcut will produce the capitalized shortcut letter. (OS X)
